{"TopicId":184328,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Program DLC: \u201CBreaking Gound\u201D Grand Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"UomoCapra","CreatedById":167737,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-21T21:45:23Z","PageNum":7,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"EchoLima","CreatedById":61992,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T03:30:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223599099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221557889796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmy\uFEFF \uFEFFfear is that the new science experiments will just be a variant on\uFEFF surface \uFEFFsam\uFEFFp\uFEFFl\uFEFFe\uFEFFs and\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E not unlock a whole new aspect of explorational \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eactivities\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe part description suggests the experiments will be time based so there\u0027s that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow else would you propose the science experiments be changed?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T04:11:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223599099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221557889796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n56 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter watching the few videos posted my fear is that the new science experiments will just be a variant on surface samples and not unlock a whole new aspect of explorational activities. Time will tell.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe can also surmise that there could\u00A0be a benefit to setting these up near the surface features, which would at least create\u00A0geographic incentives to use rovers and things. Hard to guess more than that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T04:49:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223599113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221557893461\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe can also surmise that there could\u00A0be a benefit to setting these up near the surface features, which would at least create\u00A0geographic incentives to use rovers and things. Hard to guess more than that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is that the surface features are only interacted with by the camera on a boom thing you see in the BG Logo, and on the Rover teaser pics; maybe a traditional \u0022surface sample\u0022 done by a Kerbal as well.\u00A0 The other 3 deployable science experiments are just biome-specific ones that are time-based, benefit from being deployed by a scientist Kerbal, and have power requirements (solar and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E-powered) to keep running.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-05-15T05:00:55Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2019 05:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by klesh\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T05:02:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223599125\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221557895770\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klesh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, klesh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is that the surface features are only interacted with by the camera on a boom thing you see in the BG Logo, and on the Rover teaser pics; maybe a traditional \u0022surface sample\u0022 done by a Kerbal as well.\u00A0 The other 4 deployable science experiments are just biome-specific ones that are time-based, benefit from being deployed by a scientist Kerbal, and have power requirements (solar and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E-powered) to keep running.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm yeah perhaps I\u2019m reading to much into the description that we\u2019ll be able to study the features \u201Cand\u201D use the rover arm, \u00A0implying other experiments will work on/near them. I hope I\u2019m not. Seems like it\u00A0would diminish the incentive to seek them out if only one experiment utilized them.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-05-15T05:03:52Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2019 05:03  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Pthigrivi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T05:07:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223599127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221557896539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm yeah perhaps I\u2019m reading to much into the description that we\u2019ll be able to study the features \u201Cand\u201D use the rover arm, \u00A0implying other experiments will work on/near them. I hope I\u2019m not. Seems like it\u00A0would diminish the incentive to seek them out if only one experiment utilized them.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy thought behind that is we\u0027ve not seen these deployable ones put anywhere near a surface feature (yet).\u00A0 Also, its 3 deployables not 4 as I was going off memory.\u00A0 This is my accounting of them so far:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HjUcAq5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HjUcAq5.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T08:36:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/144828-gameslinx/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022144828\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/144828-gameslinx/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gameslinx\u003C/a\u003E I think you are wrong to conclude that 95% of the added functionality is already covered. The reason is what I think is a fundamental lack of understanding of what squad does which cannot be achieved by modders. One thing that separates the modders from squad developers is that squad have access to the core engine code and are able to extend it in the best possible way. Modders are only able to program against existing code. They can extend by programming around it but you always end up with a compromise of what you really want. A prime example is Infernal robotics. Yes, it allowed you to make robotics vehicles but it came at the expense of several unsolvable issues that could not be resolved by the IR team. Only Squad has the ability to extend the engine in such a way that these problems are much better addressed. Another thing they introduce are the new mechanics that can be used by modders to make their existing mods better. A good example of this the data collection over time which surely looks like something that will make science experiments potentially a lot better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-05-17T07:15:11Z\u0022 title=\u002205/17/2019 07:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMay 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by FreeThinker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T19:05:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way, is the DLC \u0022Braking ground\u0022 or \u0022Breaking Gound\u0022? (referring to this thread\u0027s title)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-05-15T19:30:54Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2019 07:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Jestersage\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Random Kerbonaut","CreatedById":196468,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T19:13:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBreaking Ground\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-15T21:19:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting video on social media:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed345647060\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/240760572609841/posts/2440985369254006/\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder what the interface for moving the parts is like?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedB